            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] his [...]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">Shi Liu said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">"I am an insignificant official of the old (?) state of Qi. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">There was nobody that could make plans about it (?) [=I am unable to make plans?]. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">"Hearing your words I have been greatly shocked </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">and I don't know what to do" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">"Good! </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en">Facing a task and being shocked </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en">this is not [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">[...] once he reaches his end (?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">his son will succeed him, (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">(after all his son is) his second self. (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">Now, having the son (or: a sage?) leading it (=the state?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">ruling over it, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">the best is to choose him (?). </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">Shi Liu said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">"What is referred to as 'the eight'?" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">"To be false and deceitful inside, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">to indulge in sex and alcohol </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">to emphasize bells and tripods, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">to appreciate great buildings and halls </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">indulging in carriages and hunting, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">starting lawsuits </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.10" xml:lang="en">this is how (the people) are lost </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.11" xml:lang="en">one cannot but guard against it. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-3a.12" xml:lang="en"> </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en">if you will enact (public) works </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en">the people will get benefits </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en">the state and the families will therefore be at peace </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en">if you will not enact (public) works </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en">the people [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en">[...] must necessarily imperil the state and the families </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en">then one would (?) soil (the memory) of Yu and Tang </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en">if one (instead) studies (the model of) Yu and Tang </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en">since there has first been a people </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en">there has not yet been anybody who could stand on top of the earth (or: sow a seed of grain) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en">and who could (?) avoid misfortune </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en">not [...] </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en">Shi Liu said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en">"What is referred to as trust, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en">what is referred to as respect?" </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en">The master said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en">"Respect, is to observe other people's countenance </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en">to look at what they desire and [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#chris" modified="2020-11-04T21:08:50.175+09:00"> and act in accordance with it (?),</seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en">[…] People cannot be humiliated. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en">what the multitude establishes, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en">nobody can undo; </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en">what the multitude x (detest?), </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en">nobody can exalt [...] </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en">being extremely able to listen (?) </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0087_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en">and understanding antiquity. </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
      </body>
